Israel Stocks: Oil Refineries, Sunflower Sustainable Investments

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-03-10T11:52:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/israel-stocks-oil-refineries-sunflower-sustainable-investments.html
  Israel ’s TA-25 Index gained for the
first time in three days, advancing 0.2 percent to 1,255.22 at
12:43 p.m. in Tel Aviv. The gauge has lost 1.4 percent this
week.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Oil Refineries Ltd. (ORL IT) retreated 2.2 percent to 2.342
shekels, headed for the lowest close in three months. Israel’s
biggest refiner was lowered to “market perform” from
“outperform” at Clal Finance Brokerage Ltd. and to “market
perform” from “buy” at Psagot Investment House Ltd.    Sunflower Sustainable Investments Ltd. (SNFL)   rose to
the highest level this month, increasing 1 percent to 12.12
shekels. The developer of photovoltaic solar-energy projects
agreed to invest 30 million shekels ($8.4 million) to build
Israeli projects.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in  Tel Aviv  at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
